org.jemmy.dock

Annotation Type DockInfo


  • @Target(value=TYPE)
@Documented
public @interface DockInfo
    This should be used on classes - inheritors of Wrap class to give annotation processor some information.
    Author:
    shura
    See Also:
    Wrap, DockGenerator

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      boolean anonymous
      Should generated wrap() method return this class or Wrap and also should there be a constructor with one parameter - the wrap.
      boolean generateSubtypeLookups
      Should there be extra constructors which take another lookup criteria - a class of a desired control? That class must be a subtype of the one wrapped by the wrap class annotated with this annotation.
      boolean multipleCriteria
      Should the lookup constructors have LookupCriteria<Type>... parameter or the LookupCriteria<Type> parameter.
      java.lang.String name
      Desired name of the dock class, should one be generated.

    • Element Detail

      • name

        public abstract java.lang.String name
        Desired name of the dock class, should one be generated. Usually empty ("", as nulls are not allowed) in which case the calculated value is taken whatever logic annotation processor decides to use.
        Default:
        ""

      • generateSubtypeLookups

        public abstract boolean generateSubtypeLookups
        Should there be extra constructors which take another lookup criteria - a class of a desired control? That class must be a subtype of the one wrapped by the wrap class annotated with this annotation.
        Default:
        false

        Default:
        false

      • multipleCriteria

        public abstract boolean multipleCriteria

        Default:
        true
